The animation involves a single line that animates on scroll, following a predefined SVG path. The path contains multiple segments (11 in total), with a dot that follows the line, and the animation is split across 3 breakpoints: • Desktop • Tablet • Mobile (with 11 tailored media queries for specific device widths) It would be great If you can make it responsive on different widths on mobile without using 11 media queries from 768px down to 323px it's a tedious process... Also the animation doesnt have to be made with GSAP, if you can create the animation in an alternative way and works great I am all for it, it is up to you if you want to fix the code or start from scratch. Current Status: I’ve already developed a working version of the animation using: • GSAP + ScrollTrigger + MotionPathPlugin • CSS custom properties for dynamic coordinates • SVG gradients for path strokes However, I am facing two critical issues on mobile that need to be fixed: Issues to Solve: 1.
